This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for opinion summarization from online product reviews. The paper uses neural networks and weak supervision to identify salient opinions and form extractive summaries. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for identifying relevant opinions, which makes cs.IR a likely sub-category as well. The use of neural networks and machine learning also suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves human evaluation of the generated summaries, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible sub-category.
